race.description: Affinity Electrical Technologies Single Gaze Hcp
race.comment: KIMBERLEY SECRETS (2) wasn't at her best last start but is a mare with genuine talent. She should appreciate some give in the ground and has the pace to offset a wide draw. Despite the big weight, her class can shine through. MY LAST HOORAY (9) has been hitting the line strongly all campaign without breaking through. From a better draw he can settle closer, and with his sharp turn of foot he looks a real threat. VELLA FOX (5) has returned in excellent order, following his determined win here with a strong effort chasing at Albury. He's at peak fitness now, though will need luck from the gate. PRESIDENT (4) was brave winning two back at Hawkesbury before finding it too tough in town. Easier here, and on best efforts he can bounce back. URAFIKI (6) impressed fresh at Moruya before failing at Randwick. Capable of a rebound and shouldn't be dismissed.
